      • equalsAnswer

        public boolean equalsAnswer(int answerNum,
                            java.lang.String expectedAnswer)
        Compare the answer with the expected answer. Note that this method is very unforgiving in that it requires the exact same format for the expected answer, including the order of variables.

      • returnSkolemStmt

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> returnSkolemStmt(java.lang.String skolem,
                                                                     java.util.ArrayList<ProofStep> proofSteps)
        Looks for skolem function from proofsteps if query is not given. There are two types of skolem functions: one with arguments, for instance: (sk0 Human123) or one without, for example: sk2 We need to find either of these in the proofs to see what relationship it goes into

      • tallyAxioms

        public static void tallyAxioms(java.lang.String file)
        Tally the number of appearances of a particular axiom label in a file. This is intended to be used to analyse E output that looks for contradictions, with the intuition that axioms that appear in most or all of the contractions found are the source of the problem.
